.TH "ocs_create_linked_list_from_sg" 9 "ocs_create_linked_list_from_sg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ocs_create_linked_list_from_sg \- Create OCS DMA linked list from SG list.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ocs_create_linked_list_from_sg
.BI "(const struct ocs_aes_dev *aes_dev "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *sg "  ","
.BI "int sg_dma_count "  ","
.BI "struct ocs_dll_desc *dll_desc "  ","
.BI "size_t data_size "  ","
.BI "size_t data_offset "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "aes_dev" 12
The OCS AES device the list will be created for.
.IP "sg" 12
The SG list OCS DMA linked list will be created from. When
passed to this function, \fIsg\fP must have been already mapped
with \fBdma_map_sg\fP.
.IP "sg_dma_count" 12
The number of DMA-mapped entries in \fIsg\fP. This must be the
value returned by \fBdma_map_sg\fP when \fIsg\fP was mapped.
.IP "dll_desc" 12
The OCS DMA dma_list to use to store information about the
created linked list.
.IP "data_size" 12
The size of the data (from the SG list) to be mapped into the
OCS DMA linked list.
.IP "data_offset" 12
The offset (within the SG list) of the data to be mapped.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative error code otherwise.
